The following messages contain information and source code for the
QP solver bqpd. The next message contains a compressed tar'ed
file called bqpd.tar.Z. To install bqpd follow the instructions
below (this applies to UNIX users only):

   (1) Save the file bqpd.tar.Z from your mail tool.
   (2) uncompress bqpd.tar.Z
   (3) tar xf bqpd.tar

This will unpack the bqpd solver into the current directory.
It contains the following files:

   (1) SQP_bqpd.tex, a LaTeX file of the bqpd manual.
   (2) The Fortran 77 source code for bqpd.

        auxil.f			bqpd.f   		denseA.f    
	denseL.f    	    	sparseA.f    		sparseL.f    	    
	util.f       

	QPdrivers.f		QPdriverd.f

   (3) A make file (make_qp) that compiles/links the sparse QP solver.
   (4) An example sparse data file (avgas.s)

To run the example QP problem

   (1) Type "make -f make_qp" without the "".
   (2) Type "xxx" to run avgas; type "avgas 6 1 1" at the prompt.
   (3) Next you will be prompted for the Hessian matrix parameters.
       In the example, the Hessian is a tridiagonal matrix with constant
       diagonal and off-diagonal entries.  Type "4 -1" or "0 0" for LP.
